725102f-a.text:
20th Road, north side, at 37th Avenue, showing several new homes built by the Atlantic Coast Builders Inc.
1920's

725270f-a.text:
37th Street (center of view), south from 20th Road (O1d Bowery Bay Road), to Twenty-first Ave. showing at the left the site of the old Francis D. Kouwenhoven house.
May 1929.
Eugene L. Arbruster Collection.

725103f-b.text:
(1)
20th Road (0ld Bowery Bay Road), east from 37th Street, showing in the foreground the Francis Duryea Kouwenhoven house, which was demolished in May 1929.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing also a three story frame house at the N.E.
Corner of 20th Road and 38th Street.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
